```

The first parameter of "InterlockedExchanged" is defined as "LONG volatile *" for 64 bit MingW

The following change results in successful compilation but I'm not sure *dst should be an int at all on 64 bit systems.
```
int CRYPTO_atomic_store_int(int *dst, int val, CRYPTO_RWLOCK *lock)
{
#if (defined(NO_INTERLOCKEDOR64))
