With the new X509 APIs returning const pointers, using these pointers with other APIs is now more difficult without casting away the const.

Consider the snippet from our code: 

    const X509_NAME *xn = X509_get_subject_name(info->x509);
    if (!xn)
    {
        continue;
    }

    /* Don't add duplicate CA names */
    if (sk_X509_NAME_find(cert_names, xn) == -1)
    {
        xn = X509_NAME_dup(xn);
        if (!xn)
        {
            continue;
        }
        sk_X509_NAME_push(cert_names, xn);
    }

This uses a ` STACK_OF(X509_NAME) *cert_names` to keep track of certificates names and to see if there are duplicates. With the current APIs `sk_X509_NAME_find` and `sk_X509_NAME_push` require casting away the const. This is probably okay for sk_X509_NAME_push.

Another solution would be to be a able to create a stack of const X509 names.

